<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"  xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:scilab="http://www.scilab.org" xml:lang="en" xml:id="xcos_blocks_info">
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>xcos_blocks_info</refname>
    <refpurpose>Extract information about blocks in the Xcos compiled data structure.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>info = xcos_blocks_info(cpr)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Arguments</title>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">cpr :</emphasis> a data strucure
          generated by the <link
          linkend="xcos_compile">xcos_compile</link> function.
        </para>
      </listitem>
       <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">info :</emphasis> a 2D array of
          strings. Each row contains information about one block.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      This function produces a table of character strings. Each row contains the information relative to one block:
    </para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">block number :</emphasis> the index of the block in the cpr.sim.funs array
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">simulation function :</emphasis> the name of the block's simulation function
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">uid :</emphasis> the unique identifier of the block
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">rpar index :</emphasis> the index
          range of the block's real parameters array in cpr.sim.rpar
          array.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">ipar index :</emphasis> the index
          range of the block's integer parameters array in
          cpr.sim.ipar array.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">opar index:</emphasis> the index
          range of the block's object parameters array in
          cpr.sim.opar array.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">z index :</emphasis> the index
          range of the block's real discrete state array in cpr.state.z
          array.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">oz index :</emphasis>  the index
          range of the block's object discrete state array in cpr.state.oz
          array.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">x index :</emphasis> the index
          range of the block's continuous state array in cpr.state.x
          array.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
 </refsection>
  
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
    importXcosDiagram("SCI/modules/xcos/demos/IVPD.zcos")
    importXcosDiagram("~/IVPD1.zcos")
    cpr=xcos_compile(scs_m);
    Block_table=xcos_blocks_info(cpr);
    editvar Block_table;
    ]]></programlisting>
   </refsection>
